.IX Title "cgSetIntStateAssignment 3"
.TH cgSetIntStateAssignment 3 "Cg Toolkit 3.0" "perl v5.10.0" "Cg Core Runtime API"
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH "NAME"
\&\fBcgSetIntStateAssignment\fR \- set the value of an int state assignment
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  #include <Cg/cg.h>
\&
\&  CGbool cgSetIntStateAssignment( CGstateassignment sa,
\&                                  int value );
.Ve
.SH "PARAMETERS"
.IX Header "PARAMETERS"
.IP "sa" 8
.IX Item "sa"
A handle to a state assignment of type \fB\s-1CG_INT\s0\fR.
.IP "value" 8
.IX Item "value"
The value to which \fBsa\fR will be set.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
.IX Header "RETURN VALUES"
Returns \fB\s-1CG_TRUE\s0\fR if it succeeds in setting the state assignment.
.PP
Returns \fB\s-1CG_FALSE\s0\fR otherwise.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBcgSetIntStateAssignment\fR sets the value of a state assignment of int type.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.IX Header "EXAMPLES"
\&\fIto-be-written\fR
.SH "ERRORS"
.IX Header "ERRORS"
\&\fB\s-1CG_INVALID_STATE_ASSIGNMENT_HANDLE_ERROR\s0\fR is generated if \fBsa\fR is not a valid state assignment.
.PP
\&\fB\s-1CG_STATE_ASSIGNMENT_TYPE_MISMATCH_ERROR\s0\fR is generated if \fBsa\fR is not
a state assignment of an int type.
.PP
\&\fB\s-1CG_ARRAY_SIZE_MISMATCH_ERROR\s0\fR is generated if \fBsa\fR is an array and not a scalar.
.SH "HISTORY"
.IX Header "HISTORY"
\&\fBcgSetIntStateAssignment\fR was introduced in Cg 1.5.
